The Pontryagin dual of a compact monoid `M`, defined as the space of continuous monoid homomorphisms from `M` to `UnitAddCircle` (the circle group $\mathbb{R}/\mathbb{Z}$), is discrete. This is a specific instance of the general result that `ContinuousMonoidHom M N` is discrete when `M` is compact and `N` has "no small subgroups" (NSS). Since `UnitAddCircle` is a Lie group (specifically a 1-dimensional torus), it satisfies the `NoSmallSubgroups` property. Mathlib provides the theorem `ContinuousMonoidHom.discreteTopology` which captures this logic.

